      <item>
        <title>Permanently Disable Tor Auto-Start</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[entr0py]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <aside class="quote" data-post="2" data-topic="2195">
<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img alt="" width="20" height="20" src="//forums.whonix.org/user_avatar/forums.whonix.org/patrick/40/17_1.png" class="avatar"> Patrick:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>(Which sets DisableNetwork 1 in /etc/tor/torrc.)</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>I’d like to configure so I am required to start Tor <strong>manually on every boot</strong> (not just one time).</p>
<p>IIUC, using whonixsetup would require changing to <code>DisableNetwork 0</code> after every boot and changing back to <code>DisableNetwork 1</code> at each shutdown.</p>
          <p><a href="http://forums.whonix.org/t/permanently-disable-tor-auto-start/2195/3">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
